description._content: Four unidentified males (one possibly John Berghofer), standing in front of Mt. York Pavilion, a neo-Classical style concrete structure with eight Doric columns, a domed canopy and central trachyte tablet. Erected 1913 as part of First Crossing Centenary Celebrations. This image is part of a collection entitled ‘Blue Mountains - Monuments and Celebrations', which is available to view on the Royal Australian Historical Society's Historypin Channel. Access the collection at the following link: www.historypin.com/channels/view/id/48441/#|collections/v... Please feel free to comment on this or any of the other images in the collection. If you have more accurate information regarding the location and/or date of the image, we would love to hear from you!
